pr_review_comment_body:
Suggest to rename to `test_class_does_not_have_choices_as_attributes` - the intention here is to check that we don't generate `choice-one` which doesn't include in the YANG schema path.

i.e.,

```
container ca {
  choice a-choice {
     case a { 
       leaf ch-one { type string; }
     }
     case b { 
       leaf ch-two { type string; }
    }
  }
}
```

results in schema paths that are `/ca/ch-one` and `/ca/ch-two`, so we want to make sure that the `a-choice`, `a` and `b` statements don't get erroneously translated into an attribute of `ca`.

We could just treat "no content-type" as json, and only read `request.POST` if the header is one of 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded', 'multipart/form-data'

I believe a proper content type is going to be required for that anyway, right?

So form could be 

```python

@property 
def form(self):
    if self.request.headers.get('Content-Type') in FORM_TYPES:
       return request.POST
    return {}
```

